        "Build an infection timeline for a primary bacterial infection: day 0 infection → minutes: complement activation; hours 1–4: neutrophil arrival and phagocytosis; hours 4–24: macrophage activation and cytokine production; day 1–2: dendritic cell antigen presentation in lymph node; day 2–4: T cell activation and proliferation; day 5–7: B cell activation and IgM production; day 10–14: IgG production and affinity maturation; day 21: pathogen cleared; day 21+: memory cell maintenance. Annotate each phase with the rate-limiting step.",
