        "Observe complement-mediated haemolysis in a quantitative assay (or via data): sheep red blood cells are coated with antibody (to activate classical complement pathway), then incubated with different dilutions of complement (guinea pig serum). At each dilution, measure haemolysis (absorbance at 541 nm — haemoglobin released). Plot the sigmoid dose-response curve. Identify the CH50 (complement dilution producing 50% lysis). Connect this quantitative assay to the concept of complement cascade amplification — small amounts of upstream complement produce large downstream effects."
