        "Create a substrate-product tracing table for carbon atoms: one glucose (6C) → track through glycolysis → 2 pyruvate (3C each) → alcoholic fermentation: 2 acetaldehyde (2C) + 2 CO2 (1C) → 2 ethanol (2C) + 2 CO2 (1C); vs lactic acid fermentation: 2 lactate (3C each), no carbon lost. The table confirms carbon accounting and clarifies why lactic acid fermentation retains all six carbons while alcoholic fermentation releases two as CO2."
