        "Pyruvate fate matching drill: given ten cell types or conditions (e.g. 'red blood cell at rest', 'sprinting fast-twitch muscle fibre', 'Saccharomyces cerevisiae in dough', 'hepatocellular carcinoma cell in well-oxygenated tumour margin'), write the expected pyruvate fate and enzyme(s) for each within 60 seconds. Check and repeat.",
        "Connection mapping sprint: given a glycolytic intermediate (e.g. glucose-6-phosphate, pyruvate, glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate), list within 90 seconds: (a) which step produces it; (b) which step consumes it in glycolysis; (c) which other pathways it can enter; (d) one clinical consequence of its accumulation. Check and repeat with a different intermediate."
