        "Make a card for each phosphoryl transfer compound on the scale: front = compound name, back = ΔG°' of hydrolysis + position on scale relative to ATP (above/below) + whether it donates to ATP or accepts from ATP + biological context. Five cards: PEP, creatine phosphate, ATP, glucose-1-phosphate, glucose-6-phosphate.",
        "Make a 'common mistakes' card set for energy coupling: front = the incorrect statement (e.g. 'ATP contains energy in high-energy bonds'), back = why wrong + correct version + anchor. Cards: ATP bond misconception / ΔG°' = ΔG confusion / uncoupler = inhibitor / FADH₂ = NADH for ATP / Complex II pumps protons. Review before every practice exam."
