        "Make a 'mechanism of action' card for each autoantibody functional type: front = mechanism type (blocking receptor, stimulating receptor, opsonisation, immune complex, complement activation); back = definition + disease example + predicted clinical effect + whether plasmapheresis would be effective + why. This forces mechanistic rather than rote understanding of autoantibody pathology.",
        "Make a 'common mistake' correction card for each major misconception: front = the incorrect statement (e.g. 'Type 1 diabetes is caused by eating too much sugar'); back = why it is wrong + the correct mechanistic explanation + the specific cellular event that was confused. Review these before every practice exam."
