        "For antibiotic resistance mechanisms: 'PRED-TB' — Permeability reduced (porin loss); Ribosome modification; Efflux pumps; Degradation by enzyme (β-lactamase); Target modification (PBP2a, D-Ala-D-Lac); Bypass route. Test by naming a specific organism example for each.",
        "For the five immunoglobulin classes in order of serum concentration: 'Good Mice Are Extremely Diligent' — IgG (most abundant), IgM, IgA, IgE, IgD. For function: IgG = Guards (opsonisation, complement, crosses placenta); IgM = Massive (pentamer, first response, best complement activator); IgA = Airways/secretions (mucosal immunity); IgE = Eczema/allergy; IgD = Developmental (naive B cell surface receptor, function unclear).",
