        "For proton pumping at the ETC complexes: 'I pump 4, II pumps none, III pumps 4, IV pumps 2' — remember 4-0-4-2. Total = 10 protons pumped per NADH entering at Complex I. Use this to understand why FADH2 (which enters at Complex II and bypasses the first pump) generates fewer ATP.",
